description.en: Ontology designed for collecting and inferring the parameters required to create a simulation-based Health Technology Assesment
description.es: Ontología diseñada para recopilar e inferir los parámetros necesarios para crear una evaluación de tecnología sanitaria basada en simulación

abstract.value: This ontology provides a structured framework for the interoperability of health economics data used to create models. The ontology represents all the concepts and relationships involved in health technology assessment, including the characterization of the disease and its development, the population affected, and the interventions applied.

comment.en: An expression that defines a probablity distribution
The way a disease, development, manifestation or stage appears, i.e., the conditions that must be met to lead to any of these.

label.en: Expression for a Normal probability distribution
label.es: Expresión para distribución de probabilidad Normal

comment.en: Unbounded and symmetric continuous probability distribution, characterized by two parameters: average, that falls in the mode of the distribution, and standard deviation.
A set of disease progressions

label.es: Conjunto de progresiones de enfermedad alternativas

comment.undefined: A set of disease progressions which are treated as mutually exclusive alternatives, e.g., a mild and a severe development of certain disease

comment.en: Parameter with a fixed (no-uncertainty) value
Long-lasting or frequently recurring set of signs and symptoms
Generic individual to represent a utility with unknown calculation method

label.en: Expression for a Beta probability distribution
label.es: Expresión para distribución de probabilidad Beta

comment.en: Continuous probability distributions defined on the interval [0, 1] parametrized by two positive shape parameters, alfa and beta, generally estimated from the number of 'cases' and 'no cases' from an event
A disease with very low  prevalence

comment.undefined: The way a treatment, drug, test... is applied. It defines a period of time (range), dose, frequency, etc.

comment.en: A strategy related to the identification of persons potentially suffering a disease among a population
A model item that has at least one associated treatment cost or line-of-therapy

label.es: Modelo de simulación de eventos discretos

comment.en: A model based on discrete events and entities
A model item that has at least one associated utility, i.e., it must be taken into account when computing the effectiveness of the cost-effectiveness analysis
An intervention driven by a set of drugs and/or treatments
Certain progression of a Disease that comprises a specific set of manifestations or a set of pathways to such manifestations
Parameters used for computing outcomes or characterize certain class. They have a source, a geographical context, year, description and value
A model item that has at least one associated follow-up cost or strategy
Parameter which value is computed using an expression, generally dependent on other parameters
An intervention intended to establish the presence/absence of certain disease or condition
An intervention to identifiy the subset of population who may have certain disease or condition and require further testing to obtain a final diagnosis

label.es: Conjunto de progresiones de enfermedad secuenciales

comment.undefined: A set of disease progressions that appear sequentially, e.g., the stages of a cancer

comment.en: Symptoms or signs of a disease. They may be chronic or acute

label.es: Parámetro con incertidumbre de primer orden

comment.en: Parameter which value has first-order uncertainty, i.e., the value for each individual is not fixed

comment.es: A strategy related to the diagnosis of a disease

comment.en: Any non-drug intervention used to treat a disease or manifestation
The cost of any component of the model (intervention, treatment, disease progression...)
A phase or step in the progression of a disease
A natural or synthetic remedy for a disease or manifestation

comment.es: A strategy related to the follow-up of a disease or condition

comment.en: A model based on a decision tree
Tests performed to monitor the state of a patient
A model item that can be put in a group
An model based on using multiple agents
A group of model items. Useful to categorize or 'putting together' manifestations (e.g. all the eye-related manifestations of diabetes) or other model items
A container to define all the items that conform a model that can be simulated
Any component of a model
Data type to express costs
A parameter related to the epidemiology (prevalence, incidence...) of a disease or condition

label.es: Parámetro con incertidumbre de segundo orden

comment.en: Parameter which value has second-order uncertainty, i.e. the precise value is not known and is subject to uncertainty. For example, the actual value of the effectiveness of a treatment could have been derived from a metaanalysis of several studies and being defined by an average but also confidence intervals

Any type of disease or health condition that a person may suffer. Since diseases may have or not costs, utilities... all of these properties has been explicitly defined with cardinality 'min 0' as an hint for the ontology users

comment.es: A strategy related to the detection of a disease

comment.en: Sudden or rapid appearance of clinical signs or symtoms, in general with a short and intense course

label.en: Expression for a Uniform probability distribution
label.es: Expresión para distribución de probabilidad Uniforme

comment.en: A bounded continuous probability distribution, where the ocurrence of an event is equally probable inside the defined limits

label.en: Expression for an Expnential probability distribution
label.es: Expresión para distribución de probabilidad Exponencial

comment.en: Continuous probability distribution that describes the time between events in a Poisson process, i.e. a process in which events occur continuously and independently at a constant average rate
Clinical parameters that define the state of a patient and whose value may modify the evolution of the Disease and/or specific manifestations

label.en: Expression for a Gamma probability distribution
label.es: Expresión para distribución de probabilidad Gamma

comment.en: Continuous distribution of probability generally used to model costs, characterized by two parameters: alpha (shape) and lamba (scale)

label.en: Expression for a Bernoulli probability distribution
label.es: Expresión para distribución de probabilidad de Bernoulli

comment.en: A discrete (0-1) probability distribution with just one parameter (the probability of an event)

label.es: Conjunto de progresiones de enfermedad coexistentes

comment.undefined: A set of disease progressions which can coexist at the same time, e.g. seizures and skin problems.

comment.en: Any way in which a disease can progress: manifestations, symptoms, stages...

comment.es: A way of defining a series of steps required to treat, detect or follow-up a disease or condition
A strategy related to the treatment of a disease or condition

label.es: Tipo del elemento de datos medible

comment.en: Type for datas items that are measureable

label.en: Expression for a Poisson probability distribution
label.es: Expresión para distribución de probabilidad de Poisson

comment.en: Discrete probability distribution used to model the number of events occurring within a given time interval. It is defined by a real number (lambda).

Some kind of treatment, drug, surgical procedure... used to modify the development of a Disease. In the context of this ontology, interventions are the comparing options in the decision-making process

The nature of the values of a parameter, i.e., whether it is a constant, calculated, or characterizes uncertainty somehow. This must be used to define parameters together with 'Parameter' or any of its subclasses, i.e. an individual defining the cost of a drug should be subclass of both 'Cost' and 'DeterministicParameter'

Language used to define an expression in a string. Generally used to compute something from other items of the model. Only the predefined languages are allowed, but future versions of the ontology may include more.
The self-perceived utility (or disutility) of a health state, used to compute quality-adjusted life years
The type to define the nature of a data item, either its statistic nature (probability, relative risk...) or some characteristic (currency, utility...)
Model based on Markov states and transitions
A model item that has at least one associated cost, i.e., it must be taken into account when computing the cost of the cost-effectiveness analysis
An intervention intended to detect the presence of a disease or condition in a person

Any treatment, drug, test... that may be applied to a patient. In the context of this ontology, this class and its subclasses define resource usage to compute costs and must not be confused with the 'interventions'
The characteristics of the population which is the objective of the assessed interventions
Dosage of the indicated drug
Indicates whether a utility parameter represents a disutility or a utility

comment.undefined: The Sensitivity in epidemiology is the Probability of correctly classifying a sick individual, that is, the Probability that a positive result will be obtained in a diagnostic test for a sick subject. The Sensitivity is, therefore, the ability of the complementary test to detect the disease. Sensitivity is the percentage of true positives or the Probability that the test is positive if the disease is present; False negatives are sick subjects diagnosed as healthy.

comment.en: Defines the temporal behavior of a parameter (generally a cost or utility): if true, applies upon onset of some model item (disease, disease progression...); otherwise, it is assumed to apply annually.

By default = 1, for the Manifestations.
